Product summary OS/2 Warp, Version 3 

IBM Personal Software Products Division, Austin, Texas (800) 342-6672. 

If OS/2 Warp doesn't convince on-the-fence developers of OS/2's viability as a
platform, we don't know what will. This version tightly integrates OS/2's terrific
GUI with the bundled applications for unrivaled data sharing. 

Price: $89 for either 3.5-inch floppy disks or CD-ROM. 

Requires: Intel 80386 or compatible; 4MB of RAM (6MB recommended), 65MB of
disk space for a full installation; Windows support requires Windows 3.1 or later or
Windows for Workgroups 3.1 or later. 

Pros: Comes bundled with wide variety of competitive applications; faster than
previous versions; sophisticated GUI; terrific multitasking. 

Cons: None significant. 

